Date: 12 Aug 2000 23:44:57 -0300
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: New York State Dept. of Health West Nile Virus website, 11 Aug 2000
<http://www.health.state.ny.us/nysdoh/westnile/update/today.htm>

Sentinel chickens: First report of seroconversion
-------------------------------------------------
The first sentinel chicken seroconversion has occurred in Westchester
County. The chicken was in Somers and had been infected prior to ground
spraying operations conducted in that area. The Westchester County
Department of Health stated that Somers and communities within a two-mile
radius would not need to be re-sprayed at this time.
[Westchester County has had 12 positive birds since Feb 2000 & 6 positive
mosquito pools. - Mod.JW
