West Nile virus infected bird found in Yates County
---------------------------------------------------
A West Nile virus infected bird has been in Yates County, the first
documented positive finding in that county. [Yates county is located in
western New York State; - see updated bird map
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in Atlanta this week said
that 188 infected birds have been found this year, including 128 in New
York, 54 in New Jersey, four in Massachusetts and two in Connecticut. More
than half of the infected birds have been found since 1 Aug 2000. The
discovery of infected birds in upstate New York and Massachusetts indicated
the risk of human infection exists in a larger geographical area than in
1999. - Mod.CP.
